sentence: Stock futures were inching higher into Wednesday's open ahead of the Federal Open Market Committee minutes from the April meeting.

After reaching an all-time high for two straight days, the Dow Jones Industrial Average was mostly treading water at just 27 points above fair value, underpinned by strength in component stocks Johnson and Johnson ( JNJ ) and Apple ( AAPL ).
In corporate news, home-improvement retailer Lowe's ( LOW ) reported disappointing Q1 results a day after competitor Home Depot ( HD ) beat Q1 estimates and raised its EPS outlook.
Johnson and Johnson said its Janssen Pharmaceutical unit plans to file regulatory approval for 10 new drugs by 2019, each with the potential to earn more than $1 billion.
Also, Target ( TGT ) reported upbeat Q1 earnings and raised its FY15 earnings outlook.
Overseas markets were mixed with the Nikkei higher but Europe down on profit-taking after Tuesday's EBC-fueled rally.
A warning from a Greek official concerning his country's inability to make another payment to the IMF drove the euro lower against the dollar, and EU-zone equities into the red in sympathy.
There is no economic data today.
The April FOMC minutes will be released at 2:00ET.

(+) SRPT (+48.17%) Plans to submit rolling NDA for Eteplirsen after meeting with FDA

(+) PBY (+15.89%) Acquisition interest from Golden Gate Capital and others

(-) ETSY (-19.29%) Posts worse-than-expected Q1 loss and revenue in line with forecasts

(-) ACHN (-8.24%) Collaborating with Johnson and Johnson ( JNJ ) unit on hepatitis C treatment; downgraded at UBS to neutral from buy
